      "lineNumber": 1,
      "text": "STANDARD FORM NO. 64",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 2,
      "text": "Office Memorandum • UNITED STATES GOVERNMENT",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 3,
      "text": "TO : DIRECTOR, FBI DATE: March 22, 1950",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 4,
      "text": "FROM : GUY HOTTEL, SAC, WASHINGTON",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 5,
      "text": "SUBJECT: FLYING SAUCERS",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 6,
      "text": "INFORMATION CONCERNING",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 7,
      "text": "Flying Saucers",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 8,
      "text": "The following information was furnished to SA [REDACTED] by",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 9,
      "text": "[REDACTED]",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 10,
      "text": "An investigator for the Air Forces stated that three so-called",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 11,
      "text": "flying saucers had been recovered in New Mexico. They were",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 12,
      "text": "described as being circular in shape with raised centers, approxi-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 13,
      "text": "mately 50 feet in diameter. Each one was occupied by three bodies",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 14,
      "text": "of human shape but only 3 feet tall, dressed in metallic cloth of",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 15,
      "text": "a very fine texture. Each body was bandaged in a manner similar",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 16,
      "text": "to the blackout suits used by speed flyers and test pilots.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 17,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 18,
      "text": "According to Mr. [REDACTED] informant, the saucers were found in New",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 19,
      "text": "Mexico due to the fact that the Government has a very high-powered",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 20,
      "text": "radar set-up in that area and it is believed the radar interferes",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 21,
      "text": "with the controlling mechanism of the saucers.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 22,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 23,
      "text": "No further evaluation was attempted by SA [REDACTED] concerning the",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 24,
      "text": "above.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
